Riversand Platform provides **Download Model Excel** that downloads the specified data model synchronously. This service returns the data model binary object if the request is successful. As this is synchronous service, you can immediately start using the downloaded data for your further requirements. It returns an error message in case of invalid requests.

This topic describes how to use the **{{site.data.rdp_glossary.downloadModelExcel}}** to download the data model using a scenario. 

## Scenario

Download base data model for country "Germany".

## Request

To download the above template, you can use the REST API {{site.data.rdp_glossary.downloadModelExcel}}. In the request send the following details:

* In the query, specify the model to be downloaded. In this scenario, you want to download entityManageModel for "SKU" entity in "Germany" context with all attributes and relationships. 
* In the rsconnect -> profile, specify the appropriate [export profile](api_exp_entity_service.html).

<pre>
<code>
POST {TenantURL or ID}/api/rsConnectService/downloadModelExcel
Headers: Content-Type: application/json
Body:
{
  "params": {
    "query": {
      <span style="background-color: #FFFF00">"contexts": [</span>
        {
          "country": "Germany"
        }
      ],
      "filters": {
        "typesCriterion": [
          <span style="background-color: #FFFF00">"entityManageModel"</span>
        ]
      },
      <span style="background-color: #FFFF00">"id": "sku_entityManageModel"</span>
    },
    "fields": {
      "attributes": [
        "_ALL"
      ],
      "relationships": [
        "_ALL"
      ]
    },
    "rsconnect": {
      <span style="background-color: #FFFF00">"profiles": [</span>
        "entityModelDownload"
      ]
    }
  }
}
</code>
</pre>

## Response

Returns the binary object of the model for further processing.

{
  "response": {
    "binaryObjects": [
      {
        "id": "9415d624-482c-47a3-8920-09a64ff6acd5",
        "type": "excelObject",
        "systemInfo": {
          "tenantId": "rwtest"
        },
        "properties": {
          "fileName": "SmartExcelBaseTemplatev012.xlsm",
          "version": "0.14",
          "extension": "xlsm"
        },
        "data": {
          "blob": ""
        }
      }
    ],
    "status": "success",
    "statusDetail": {},
    "totalRecords": 1
  }

</code></pre>

For the above request, the job is submitted successfully as detailed in the **status** object. The downloaded template is part of the **data -> blob**. As displayed in the above response, you receive the following details:

* properties -> fileName: Indicates the downloaded template name.
* properties -> version: Indicates the version of the downloaded Excel.
* properties -> extension: Indicates the extension of the downloaded Excel.
* totalRecords: Indicates the total records that is received in the response.
